  <%- include('../partials/header') %>

  <main class="legal-page">
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: December 2024</p>

    <div class="highlight">
      <p><strong>What are cookies?</strong> Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit websites. They help us remember your preferences, understand how you use our site, and improve your experience.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

    <h3>1. Essential Cookies</h3>
    <p>These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. Without them, you wouldn't be able to use core features.</p>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Cookie Name</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Duration</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>session_id</td>
        <td>Maintains your shopping cart and login session</td>
        <td>Session</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>csrf_token</td>
        <td>Security protection against cross-site attacks</td>
        <td>Session</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>auth_token</td>
        <td>Keeps you logged in securely</td>
        <td>30 days</td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <h3>2. Analytics Cookies</h3>
    <p>These cookies help us understand how visitors use our website, which pages are popular, and how to improve the site.</p>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Cookie Name</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Duration</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>_ga</td>
        <td>Google Analytics - tracks unique visitors</td>
        <td>2 years</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
